*.env

# ── Core Backend Logic (proprietary — do not expose) ─────────────────
backend/core/
backend/api/
backend/utils/
backend/tests/
backend/main.py

# ── Frontend Source Logic (proprietary — do not expose) ───────────────
frontend/src/components/
frontend/src/pages/
frontend/src/hooks/
frontend/src/utils/
frontend/src/styles/
frontend/src/App.jsx
frontend/src/main.jsx

# ── Node / Frontend Build ─────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
dist/
.vite/
frontend/dist/

# ── macOS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverrideIcon
._*

# ── VS Code ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/settings.json
.vscode/launch.json
*.code-workspace

# ── Logs & Debug ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
logs/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*

# ── Misc ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.swp
*.swo
.cache/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
```

---

## What this protects

| Protected | What stays hidden |
|---|---|
| `backend/core/` | Your scraper and scoring algorithm |
| `backend/api/` | All five analysis modules |
| `backend/main.py` | App entry point and route structure |
| `frontend/src/` | All React components, pages, and utilities |
| `.env` files | Any API keys or secrets |

---

## What stays PUBLIC on GitHub

These files **will** be visible — enough to show it's a real project without giving away your code:
```
seo-now-tool/
├── README.md              ← portfolio showcase
├── LICENSE                ← your ownership
├── .gitignore             ← this file
├── backend/
│   └── requirements.txt   ← shows your tech stack
├── frontend/
│   ├── package.json       ← shows dependencies
│   ├── index.html         ← entry shell
│   ├── vite.config.js     ← build config
│   ├── tailwind.config.js ← styling config
│   └── postcss.config.js  ← build config
└── docs/                  ← any screenshots you add